parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag warning light can indicate a potential failure of the airbag system, which can lead to a loss of protection in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light is illuminated on the instrument panel
the passenger airbag warning sensor is illuminated
the airbag warning light flashes or stays on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective Takata airbags can rupture and cause serious injury or fatality in the event of a crash, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants.
symptoms: No symptoms reported
but the recall notice was received
and the parts are not available for repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to a loss of protection, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbags did not deploy in a side impact crash
the driver did not receive protection from the crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause loss of power, fires, and accidents, leading to safety risks and potential injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
burning smells
smoke
and fires; electrical components melting or overheating; warning lights illuminating; and loss of functionality in various systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Heated seat control module failures can cause fires, electrical shocks, and burns, leading to safety risks and potential injuries.
symptoms: Burning smells
smoke
and fires; overheating or melting of electrical components; and loss of functionality in heated seat systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Instrument panel cluster failures can cause loss of critical information, such as speed and gear position, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: Instrument panel cluster malfunctioning or going dark; loss of speedometer
gear position
and other critical information.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving at high speeds, leading to safety risks and potential injuries.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
engine stalling
and loss of acceleration; warning lights illuminating; and difficulty restarting the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Headlight and lighting system failures can cause reduced visibility, leading to safety risks and potential accidents.
symptoms: Headlights and other lights malfunctioning or going out; reduced visibility
especially at night or in low-light conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag and safety system failures can cause failure to deploy in the event of an accident, leading to safety risks and potential injuries.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights illuminating; failure to deploy airbags in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accumulation of condensation and moisture in the headlights can cause the bulbs to fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night or in rainy conditions.
symptoms: Water or moisture accumulation in the headlights
condensation in the headlight assembly
bulb failure
dim or reduced light output
repeated repairs
and safety risks due to reduced visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Extremely bright headlights can cause temporary blindness to oncoming drivers, especially in rainy conditions, leading to increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Blinding or disorienting glare from oncoming headlights
especially in rainy conditions.
